text: Why do programmers prefer dark mode? Because light attracts bugs.
I told my computer I needed a break… it said 'No problem — I’ll go to sleep.'
Why did the scarecrow get promoted? He was outstanding in his field.
I tried to teach my router a bedtime routine. Now it only disconnects after a story.
Why did the keyboard break up with the mouse? It felt like it was being clicked with.
I told my computer I’d clean up my files. It opened the recycle bin like, 'be my guest.'
My code was so polite today. It kept returning early.
Why don’t servers ever get lonely? They have plenty of connections.
I asked DNS for directions. It said, 'That depends—what do you *mean* by home?'
Why did the laptop bring a jacket? It heard the office was full of cold starts.
I tried to make a belt out of USB cables. Total waist of bandwidth.
My password is so strong it refuses to lift anything.
Why did the spreadsheet look confident? It had all its cells together.
I set my alarm to 'update mode.' Now it wakes me up, restarts, and forgets why.
Why did the printer get invited to every party? It really knows how to make an impression.
I bought a book on debugging. It was full of plot fixes.
Why did the cable go to school? To improve its connection skills.
My Wi-Fi and I are taking a break. It says I’m too attached.
Why did the monitor join a band? It had great screen presence.
I asked my code for a hint. It said, 'Try again.'
Why did the cloud bring an umbrella? Too many requests for showers.
I tried to make a joke about RAM… but I couldn’t remember it.
Why did the calendar feel stressed? It had too many dates.
My computer loves winter. It runs better when the fans are in season.
Why did the USB stick apply for a job? It wanted to be more than just storage.
I told my laptop to stop multitasking. It opened 12 tabs to prove it could.
Why don’t bugs ever get promoted? They keep showing up in the wrong places.
I tried to write a joke about backups. Don’t worry—I saved it for later.
Why did the helpdesk bring snacks? For the support tickets.
My mouse is very dramatic. It always makes a point.
Why did the switch feel powerful? It controlled the room’s mood lighting.
I tried to make a joke about encryption… but it’s classified.
Why did the QR code get a standing ovation? It really brought people together.
Why can't football players wear glasses on the field? Because it's a contact sport!
What do you get when you mix alcohol with literature? Tequila Mockingbird!
All the toilets in the NYPD headquarters have been stolen... The police apparently have nothing to go on!
When is a piece of wood like a King? When it is a ruler!
Why don't cows have money? Because the farmers milk them dry!
What did the drummer call his twin daughters? Anna One, Anna Two!
I wanted to learn how to drive a stick shift... But I couldn't find a manual.
